WEBVTT

00:02.250 --> 00:03.880
KATARA: <i>Water.</i>

00:04.840 --> 00:06.220
<i>Earth.</i>

00:06.800 --> 00:08.220
<i>Fire.</i>

00:08.890 --> 00:10.510
<i>Air.</i>

00:11.350 --> 00:14.600
<i>Long ago, the four nations
lived together in harmony.</i>

00:15.270 --> 00:18.560
<i>Then everything changed
when the Fire Nation attacked.</i>

00:19.600 --> 00:22.570
<i>Only the Avatar,
master of all four elements,</i>

00:22.650 --> 00:23.860
<i>could stop them.</i>

00:23.940 --> 00:26.860
<i>But when the world
needed him most, he vanished.</i>

00:27.240 --> 00:28.360
<i>A hundred years passed,</i>

00:28.450 --> 00:30.870
<i>and my brother and I
discovered the new Avatar,</i>

00:30.950 --> 00:32.700
<i>an airbender named Aang.</i>

00:32.910 --> 00:35.040
<i>And although his
airbending skills are great,</i>

00:35.120 --> 00:37.710
<i>he has a lot to learn before
he's ready to save anyone.</i>

00:37.790 --> 00:38.790
AANG: Oof.

00:38.870 --> 00:41.830
<i>But I believe
Aang can save the world.</i>

00:47.840 --> 00:50.050
ROKU: <i>Previously on</i> Avatar...

00:50.340 --> 00:53.640
KATARA: I can't believe we finally made it
to Ba Sing Se in one piece.

00:53.890 --> 00:59.770
I just want our new place to look nice,
in case someone brings home a lady friend.

00:59.850 --> 01:01.850
ZUKO: I don't want to make a life here.

01:02.060 --> 01:04.440
JOO DEE: Here we are,
your new home.

01:05.110 --> 01:07.070
We need to talk to the king
about the war.

01:07.150 --> 01:10.660
Your request for an audience
with the Earth King is being processed,

01:10.740 --> 01:12.780
and should be put through
in about a month!

01:13.160 --> 01:16.830
If we're gonna be here for a month,
we should spend our time looking for Appa.

01:36.720 --> 01:37.770
( CLICKING TONGUE )

01:41.480 --> 01:42.730
( CHIRPING )

01:45.610 --> 01:46.860
( GASPING )

01:46.940 --> 01:49.070
Toph, aren't you
gonna get ready for the day?

01:51.610 --> 01:52.700
( HOCKING AND SPITTING )

01:56.120 --> 01:57.200
I'm ready.

01:57.290 --> 01:58.830
You're not gonna wash up?

01:58.910 --> 02:02.250
You've got a little dirt on your...
Everywhere, actually.

02:02.670 --> 02:06.460
You call it dirt, I call it
a healthy coating of earth.

02:06.540 --> 02:07.670
Hmm...

02:07.750 --> 02:09.130
You know what we need?

02:09.460 --> 02:11.420
A girls' day out!

02:11.800 --> 02:13.260
Do I have to?

02:13.340 --> 02:14.890
KATARA: It'll be fun.

02:19.100 --> 02:21.180
TOPH: The Fancy Lady Day Spa?

02:21.270 --> 02:23.140
Sounds like my kind of place.

02:23.600 --> 02:25.900
Are you ready for
some serious pampering?

02:26.560 --> 02:28.230
( HESITATING ) Sure, Katara.

02:28.320 --> 02:29.780
Whatever you say.

02:29.860 --> 02:31.690
As long as
they don't touch my feet.

02:36.820 --> 02:37.830
( SCRAPING )

02:38.200 --> 02:40.160
( GRUNTING AND GROWLING )

02:41.660 --> 02:42.710
Ugh!

02:42.790 --> 02:43.790
Uh...

02:49.050 --> 02:50.960
( BLOWING )

02:52.050 --> 02:53.760
( SCREAMING )

02:54.340 --> 02:56.800
( BOTH LAUGHING )

03:03.060 --> 03:04.850
( BOTH SIGHING )

03:07.110 --> 03:08.820
Well, that wasn't so bad.

03:09.070 --> 03:13.440
I'm not usually into that stuff,
but I actually feel... Girly.

03:13.700 --> 03:14.740
KATARA: I'm glad.

03:14.820 --> 03:16.990
It's about time
we did something fun together.

03:22.330 --> 03:24.000
Wow, great makeup.

03:24.080 --> 03:25.080
Thanks.

03:25.250 --> 03:26.500
For a clown.

03:27.000 --> 03:29.380
( LAUGHING )

03:30.210 --> 03:32.380
Don't listen to them.
Let's just keep walking.

03:32.710 --> 03:34.510
I think she looks cute.

03:34.590 --> 03:37.470
Like that time we put a sweater
on your pet poodle-monkey.

03:37.550 --> 03:39.720
( LAUGHTER )

03:40.720 --> 03:41.930
GIRL: Good one, Star.

03:42.520 --> 03:43.890
Let's go, Toph.

03:44.020 --> 03:46.690
TOPH: No, no,
that was a good one.

03:46.770 --> 03:48.190
"Like your poodle-monkey."

03:48.270 --> 03:49.980
( LAUGHING )

03:50.060 --> 03:51.860
You, you know what else
is a good one?

03:53.110 --> 03:54.110
( SCREAMING )

03:56.150 --> 03:57.740
Now that was funny.

03:58.950 --> 04:00.200
( SCREAMING )

04:00.740 --> 04:03.080
Those girls don't know what
they're talking about.

04:03.370 --> 04:04.540
TOPH: It's okay.

04:04.620 --> 04:06.500
One of the good things
about being blind

04:06.580 --> 04:09.880
Is that I don't have to waste my time
worrying about appearances.

04:09.960 --> 04:11.840
I don't care what I look like.

04:11.920 --> 04:14.090
I'm not looking for
anyone's approval.

04:14.590 --> 04:16.220
I know who I am.

04:16.300 --> 04:18.760
KATARA: That's what
I really admire about you, Toph.

04:19.090 --> 04:21.760
You're so strong and confident
and self-assured.

04:22.050 --> 04:23.180
( SNIFFING )

04:23.260 --> 04:25.430
And I know
it doesn't matter, but...

04:25.680 --> 04:27.190
You're really pretty.

04:27.690 --> 04:28.730
I am?

04:29.020 --> 04:30.400
Yeah, you are.

04:34.900 --> 04:38.400
TOPH: I'd return the compliment,
but I have no idea what you look like.

04:38.490 --> 04:39.700
( KATARA LAUGHING )

04:39.780 --> 04:40.990
TOPH: Thank you, Katara.

04:41.070 --> 04:42.160
KATARA: Ow!

04:55.760 --> 04:59.970
If this is for a romantic picnic,
may I suggest this lavender one?

05:00.050 --> 05:05.220
No, it's not a romantic picnic,
but it is a special occasion.

05:13.610 --> 05:16.570
IROH: The moonflower
likes partial shade.

05:24.160 --> 05:25.450
( CHILD CRYING )

05:25.540 --> 05:27.750
WOMAN: It's okay, Shh, shh, shh.

05:27.830 --> 05:29.870
WOMAN: It's okay, Shh.

05:31.170 --> 05:33.630
( MUSIC PLAYING )

05:34.380 --> 05:37.510
♪ <i>Leaves from the vine</i>

05:37.630 --> 05:40.130
♪ <i>Falling so slow</i>

05:40.260 --> 05:47.100
♪ <i>Like fragile, tiny shells</i>
<i>drifting in the foam</i>

05:47.470 --> 05:53.730
♪ <i>Little soldier boy,</i>
<i>come marching home</i>

05:54.110 --> 05:57.150
♪ <i>Brave soldier boy</i>

05:59.650 --> 06:03.240
♪ <i>Comes marching home</i> ♪

06:05.620 --> 06:06.950
Yeowch!

06:07.030 --> 06:08.330
( LAUGHING )

06:24.590 --> 06:26.220
MAN: Hey!

06:26.300 --> 06:29.640
IROH: It is usually best to
admit mistakes when they occur.

06:30.020 --> 06:32.140
And to seek to restore honor.

06:32.230 --> 06:34.150
( STOMPING )

06:34.230 --> 06:38.900
When I'm through with you kids, the window
won't be the only thing that's broken!

06:39.030 --> 06:40.480
But not this time.

06:40.570 --> 06:41.650
Run!

06:49.620 --> 06:50.870
THIEF: You.

06:51.000 --> 06:52.710
Give me all your money!

06:56.040 --> 06:57.670
What are you doing?

06:57.750 --> 06:58.960
I'm mugging you!

06:59.050 --> 07:00.420
With that stance?

07:00.500 --> 07:01.630
Wha-?

07:01.710 --> 07:03.090
What are you talking about?

07:03.170 --> 07:04.800
Just give me your money,
old man!

07:05.180 --> 07:10.220
With a poor stance, you are unbalanced,
and you can be easily knocked over.

07:12.480 --> 07:13.480
Ugh!

07:18.730 --> 07:23.530
With a solid stance, you are
a much more serious threat.

07:27.370 --> 07:28.620
Much better!

07:28.990 --> 07:33.250
But to tell you the truth,
you do not look like the criminal type.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.290
I know, I'm...

07:35.620 --> 07:36.790
I'm just confused.

07:39.290 --> 07:41.800
THIEF: So you really think
I could be a good masseur?

07:41.880 --> 07:43.170
Of course!

07:44.840 --> 07:46.090
This is so great!

07:46.720 --> 07:48.260
No one has ever believed in me.

07:48.720 --> 07:52.060
While it is always best
to believe in oneself,

07:52.140 --> 07:56.140
a little help from others
can be a great blessing.

08:20.630 --> 08:22.800
IROH: Happy birthday, my son.

08:24.670 --> 08:27.470
If only I could have helped you.

08:28.800 --> 08:32.050
♪ <i>Leaves from the vine</i>

08:32.930 --> 08:35.430
♪ <i>Falling so slow</i>

08:35.520 --> 08:41.980
♪ <i>Like fragile, tiny shells</i>
<i>drifting in the foam</i>

08:42.570 --> 08:46.320
( CRYING ) ♪ <i>Little soldier boy</i>

08:46.400 --> 08:48.110
♪ <i>Come marching home</i>

08:49.200 --> 08:52.870
♪ <i>Brave soldier boy</i>

08:52.990 --> 08:56.580
♪ <i>Comes marching home</i> ♪

09:35.080 --> 09:36.200
Hey there, fella.

09:36.580 --> 09:37.660
AANG: You look hungry.

09:37.750 --> 09:38.750
Ahh!

09:42.330 --> 09:43.460
They are hungry.

09:45.880 --> 09:49.170
The Dai Li won't give me any money
because the kids stopped coming.

09:49.590 --> 09:52.680
And the kids won't come because
my zoo's nasty and broke.

09:53.260 --> 09:54.680
What kind of animal is that?

09:54.930 --> 09:56.220
Ooh, that's a rabbiroo.

09:56.310 --> 09:59.180
I wish I could get her a big,
open prairie, like she likes.

10:00.020 --> 10:01.770
I'd let her
hop her way to happiness.

10:04.020 --> 10:06.020
- Let's do it.
- Say again?

10:06.110 --> 10:09.030
There's a big open space right
outside the walls of the city.

10:09.110 --> 10:12.280
ZOOKEEPER: But how are you
gonna transport all these wild critters?

10:12.360 --> 10:14.370
Don't worry,
I'm great with animals.

10:22.920 --> 10:25.210
( SCREAMING )

10:32.800 --> 10:34.800
( SPUTTERING )

10:35.470 --> 10:37.100
My cab-

10:38.220 --> 10:39.810
Oh, forget it.

10:40.430 --> 10:42.890
( SCREAMING )

10:52.030 --> 10:54.240
This was so much easier
in my head.

10:59.240 --> 11:00.370
( INHALING )

11:15.090 --> 11:16.090
( CRYING )

11:23.100 --> 11:25.020
Oom-oom-oom, oom-oom-oom.

11:25.850 --> 11:27.560
But you have to open this gate!

11:27.650 --> 11:28.730
Or what?

11:28.810 --> 11:29.820
Or that!

11:33.570 --> 11:35.150
Open the gate!

12:10.190 --> 12:12.570
( GRUNTING )

12:21.410 --> 12:22.660
( LAUGHING )

12:30.290 --> 12:31.630
( SQUEAKING )

12:32.250 --> 12:35.300
Well, Mr. Zookeeper, how do you
like your new facilities?

12:35.380 --> 12:37.510
Excellent job, Avatar.

12:37.590 --> 12:40.260
You should think about working
with animals for a living.

12:40.340 --> 12:43.430
CHILD 1: Mommy, Miss Snowflake
got out of the house again.

12:43.510 --> 12:44.810
( HISSING )

12:44.890 --> 12:47.310
CHILD 2: Fluffikins, what are you
doing down there?

12:47.390 --> 12:48.980
( MEOWING )

12:49.060 --> 12:52.190
On second thought, you should
probably stick to saving people.

12:52.270 --> 12:54.530
( LAUGHING NERVOUSLY )

13:10.330 --> 13:12.250
( ANIMAL GRUNTING )

13:12.960 --> 13:14.380
( FAINT CONVERSATION )

13:15.380 --> 13:16.590
What's this?

13:16.670 --> 13:18.550
"Through all the long night,

13:18.630 --> 13:21.430
"Winter moon glows
with bright love.

13:21.510 --> 13:24.010
"Sleet, her silver tears."

13:24.470 --> 13:27.220
Ahh, poetry.

13:27.310 --> 13:28.850
( GRUNTING )

13:28.930 --> 13:30.140
Augh!

13:30.230 --> 13:31.230
( WOMEN GASPING )

13:32.730 --> 13:34.270
I am so sorry.

13:34.940 --> 13:36.730
Something struck me in the rear.

13:37.740 --> 13:41.110
I just... Wound up... Here?

13:41.490 --> 13:46.240
( LAUGHING )

13:48.450 --> 13:54.380
"Five, seven, then five syllables mark
a haiku, remarkable oaf."

13:57.380 --> 14:03.640
"They call me Sokka, that is,
in the water tribe. I am not an oaf."

14:03.800 --> 14:06.220
( LAUGHING )

14:06.470 --> 14:12.440
"Chittering monkey. In the spring he
climbs treetops and thinks himself tall."

14:12.900 --> 14:14.440
Ooh...

14:14.770 --> 14:19.780
"You think you're so smart, with your
fancy little words. This is not so hard."

14:20.240 --> 14:22.110
WOMEN: Ooh...

14:22.320 --> 14:27.620
"Whole seasons are spent mastering
the form, the style. None calls it easy."

14:27.700 --> 14:33.120
"I calls it easy. Like I paddle my canoe,
I'll paddle yours, too."

14:33.460 --> 14:36.840
( LAUGHING )

14:37.290 --> 14:40.010
"There's nuts and there's fruits.

14:40.090 --> 14:44.470
"In fall, the clean plum drops,
always to be squashed."

14:46.970 --> 14:49.310
"Squish-squash sling that slang,

14:49.390 --> 14:53.520
"I'm always right back at ya,
like my... Boomerang."

14:53.850 --> 14:56.480
( LAUGHING )

15:00.860 --> 15:04.530
"That's right, I'm Sokka,
it's pronounced with an 'Okka,

15:04.610 --> 15:07.490
"'young ladies, I rocked ya."

15:10.330 --> 15:11.330
( CRICKET CHIRPING )

15:15.710 --> 15:19.130
Uh, that's one too many
syllables there, bub.

15:22.590 --> 15:23.590
Augh!

15:26.800 --> 15:27.930
Poetry.

15:40.400 --> 15:42.570
Uncle, we have a problem.

15:43.690 --> 15:45.450
One of the customers
is on to us.

15:46.240 --> 15:49.410
Don't look now, but there is
a girl over there at the corner table.

15:49.490 --> 15:51.120
ZUKO: She knows we're Fire Nation.

15:51.990 --> 15:53.660
Didn't I say don't look?

15:54.120 --> 15:55.540
IROH: You're right, Zuko.

15:55.620 --> 15:58.080
I've seen that girl in here quite a lot.

15:58.540 --> 16:02.090
Seems to me she has
quite a little crush on you.

16:02.170 --> 16:03.170
What?

16:03.260 --> 16:04.760
Thank you for the tea.

16:06.590 --> 16:07.800
What's your name?

16:08.300 --> 16:09.600
My name's Lee.

16:09.680 --> 16:11.180
My uncle and I just moved here.

16:11.600 --> 16:14.100
Hi, Lee, my name's Jin.

16:14.180 --> 16:16.100
Thank you, and, well,

16:16.690 --> 16:19.980
I was wondering if you would
like to go out some time.

16:20.060 --> 16:21.270
He'd love to.

16:21.650 --> 16:24.320
Great! I'll meet you
in front of the shop at sundown.

16:37.370 --> 16:38.500
Hey.

16:38.580 --> 16:40.080
Well, look at you.

16:40.420 --> 16:41.790
You look so cute.

16:42.250 --> 16:45.210
It took my uncle
ten minutes to do my hair.

16:50.050 --> 16:52.680
So, how do you
like the city so far?

16:52.760 --> 16:53.970
It's okay.

16:54.390 --> 16:55.970
What do you like to do for fun?

16:56.060 --> 16:57.350
Nothing.

16:57.430 --> 17:00.400
Excuse me, sir, would you
and your girlfriend care for dessert?

17:00.480 --> 17:02.270
( SCREAMING ) She is not my girlfriend!

17:08.200 --> 17:12.200
You have...
Quite an appetite for a girl.

17:12.570 --> 17:14.370
Um, thanks?

17:15.830 --> 17:20.290
So, Lee, where were you and your uncle
living before you came here?

17:20.420 --> 17:25.250
( HESITATING ) Um, well, we've been
traveling around for a long time.

17:25.340 --> 17:27.920
Oh! Why were you traveling so much?

17:28.010 --> 17:31.470
We were, uh, part of this
traveling circus.

17:31.550 --> 17:32.720
Really?

17:32.800 --> 17:34.890
What did you do?
Wait, let me guess.

17:35.760 --> 17:36.770
You juggled.

17:38.100 --> 17:39.600
Yes, I juggled.

17:39.690 --> 17:41.650
I've always wanted to
learn how to juggle.

17:41.730 --> 17:43.060
Can you show me something?

17:46.150 --> 17:47.440
Uh...

17:49.780 --> 17:51.110
Whoa, uh!

17:51.660 --> 17:53.450
I haven't practiced for a while.

17:53.530 --> 17:54.950
JIN: It's all right.

17:55.780 --> 17:59.370
Hey, I want to show you
one of my favorite places in the city.

18:00.620 --> 18:03.380
JIN: I'm so excited for you
to see the firelight fountain.

18:03.460 --> 18:05.090
The lamps make the water sparkle,

18:05.170 --> 18:08.130
and reflect in the pool
in the most beautiful way.

18:10.510 --> 18:11.720
I can't believe it!

18:11.800 --> 18:13.010
JIN: They aren't lit.

18:16.890 --> 18:17.890
Close your eyes.

18:17.970 --> 18:18.970
And don't peek.

18:37.080 --> 18:39.290
ZUKO: Okay, Now you can look.

18:39.750 --> 18:41.580
Oh, wow...

18:45.210 --> 18:46.290
What happened?

18:46.380 --> 18:47.630
How did they light?

18:47.710 --> 18:49.050
What did you...

18:59.930 --> 19:01.430
I brought you something.

19:01.770 --> 19:03.980
ZUKO: It's a coupon
for a free cup of tea.

19:04.390 --> 19:06.940
Lee, this is so sweet.

19:07.900 --> 19:09.730
Don't thank me,
it was my uncle's idea.

19:09.820 --> 19:11.900
He thinks you're our
most valuable customer.

19:11.990 --> 19:13.610
Your uncle is a good teacher.

19:15.360 --> 19:17.490
I have something for you, too.

19:17.570 --> 19:19.990
Now it's your turn
to close your eyes.

19:27.790 --> 19:28.840
JIN: What's wrong?

19:29.340 --> 19:30.500
It's complicated.

19:30.590 --> 19:31.590
I have to go.

19:43.730 --> 19:45.560
How was your night, Prince Zuko?

19:50.650 --> 19:51.650
It was nice.

20:03.500 --> 20:05.080
( APPA GROWLING )

20:06.670 --> 20:07.960
( MOMO CHIRPING )

20:20.550 --> 20:22.310
( THUNDER CRASHING )

20:22.930 --> 20:24.270
( CHIRPING )

